byline.original: By BRIAN STELTER and CLAIRE CAIN MILLER

abstract: YouTube, making expensive bet on original content, is planning to create dozens of channels featuring comedians, sports stars, musicians and other entertainers; channels will receive programming from many media companies.
snippet: The unit of Google has said it wants to create an alternative to cable television on the Internet by creating channels featuring comedians, sports stars, musicians and other entertainers.
lead_paragraph: The unit of Google has said it wants to create an alternative to cable television on the Internet by creating channels featuring comedians, sports stars, musicians and other entertainers.

headline.main: YouTube Plans to Make Big Bet on New Online Channels
